{"to":["sarah@helpinghandsunited.org"],"subject":"Re: Request for Final “Community Care Day” Details","body":"Hi Sarah,

Great to hear from you! I’ve pulled together the latest details for Community Care Day. I’ve also updated the “Community Care Day” page in our shared Notion space so you can copy/paste anything you need.

Date & Time
• Saturday, March 15 (Rain or shine)
• Volunteer arrival & set-up: 8:00–9:30 AM
• Welcome & opening remarks: 10:00 AM
• Service activities (food & clothing distribution, health screenings, job-fair booths, kids’ zone): 10:15 AM–3:30 PM
• Break / lunch rotation for volunteers: 12:00–1:30 PM (staggered)
• Closing prayer & thank-you: 3:45–4:00 PM
• Clean-up & wrap-up: 4:00–5:00 PM

Location
St. Mary’s Parish Hall & surrounding grounds, 123 Elm Street.
• Hall – Registration, indoor seating, children’s activities.
• South parking-lot tents – Food & clothing distribution.
• North lawn – Health check-up stations.
• Parish Hall classrooms 2 & 3 – Job-fair tables.

Roles Still Needed
• 4 volunteers for parking guidance (8:00–10:30 AM)
• 2 additional nurses/EMTs for the health tent (any two-hour block)
• 3 floaters to relieve other volunteers during breaks (10:00 AM–3:30 PM)

Promo Materials
Flyer (PDF & PNG) and short social-media blurb are in Notion under the “Promotion” sub-page. Feel free to circulate.

Key Contacts (day-of)
• John (me): 555-123-4567
• Facilities lead – Mark H.: 555-987-6543
• Volunteer coordinator – Ana P.: 555-222-3344

Parking / Accessibility / What to Bring
• Free parking in the north lot; overflow at Jefferson Middle School two blocks east (shuttle van every 30 min).
• Wheelchair-accessible entrances on the west side of the hall; portable ramps ordered for lawn areas.
• Participants should bring a reusable water bottle; we will provide refilling stations. Volunteers: dress in parish or HHU T-shirts if you have them and wear closed-toe shoes.

Let me know if you need any tweaks. Thanks for getting the word out, and looking forward to another rewarding day of service.

Peace,
John
St. Mary’s Parish","cc":null,"bcc":null,"execution_log_path":"data/logs/item100_execution_log.json","card_path":"data/agent_cards/item100_recipient.json"}

{"to":["sarah@helpinghandsunited.org"],"subject":"Re: Request for Final “Community Care Day” Details","body":"Hi Sarah,
